# Claude Code Rules for Adeept RaspClaws Project

## Project Overview
- **Adeept RaspClaws** - Hexapod robot control system (6-legged robot)
- Client-Server architecture: Windows GUI (Client) â†” Raspberry Pi (Server)
- Main languages: Python 3.7+ (Client), Python 3.13 (Server)

## Documentation
- **Full documentation**: Read `AGENTS.md` for development environment, architecture, network setup, troubleshooting
- **Feature history**: See `Docu/Changes/` directory (FT1-FT46 feature documentation)
- **Keyboard shortcuts**: `Docu/KEYBOARD_SHORTCUTS.md`

## Important Files
- **Protocol constants**: `protocol.py` - ALL command strings are defined here as constants
  - Use constants (e.g., `CMD_FORWARD`) instead of string literals
  - Import: `from protocol import *`
- **Client**: `Client/GUI.py` (Tkinter GUI), `Client/Footage-GUI.py` (Video window)
- **Server**: `Server/GUIServer.py` (main server), `Server/Move.py` (movement control), `Server/FPV.py` (video streaming)

## Code Guidelines
- **Always use protocol constants** from `protocol.py` for commands and status messages
- **Prefer editing existing files** over creating new ones
- **No emojis** in code unless explicitly requested
- **Read files before editing** - use Read tool first
- **Test before committing** - especially movement and servo commands

## Git Workflow
- Main branch: `master`
- Old main branch: `master-old` (use for PRs if needed)
- Commit format: Descriptive messages with `Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>`

## Feature Documentation
- For new features: Create `Docu/Changes/FT<nr> - <description>_<language>.md`
- Languages: `_de` (German), `_en` (English)
- Update existing FT files when modifying features (not for every bugfix, just major changes)

## Network Configuration
- Server IP: Configurable in `Client/IP.txt`
- Ports: TCP 10223 (commands), ZMQ 5555 (video stream)
- SSH tunnel support available for firewall-restricted environments

## Hardware Notes
- PCA9685 PWM Controller: I2C address **0x40** (not 0x5F!)
- ADS7830 ADC: I2C address **0x48** (battery monitoring)
- Mock mode available for development without hardware
